Template: mirror/no-default
Type: boolean
Default: true
# :sl2:
_Description: Go back and try a different mirror?
 The specified (default) Parrot version (${RELEASE}) is not available from
 the selected mirror. Select a different release or go back and select another mirror.

Template: mirror/bad
Type: error
# :sl2:
_Description: Bad archive mirror
 An error has been detected while trying to use the specified Parrot archive
 mirror.
 .
 Possible reasons for the error are: incorrect mirror specified;
 * mirror is not available (possibly due to an unreliable network connection);
 * mirror is broken (for example because an invalid Release file was found);
 * mirror does not support the correct Parrot version.
 .
 How to read the full log:
 Open a terminal window and check the content of /var/log/syslog
 Or alternatively press CTRL+ALT+f4 to see the log file. You can go back with
 CTRL+ALT+F1 (console installer) or CTRL+ALT+F5 (gtk installer).
 .
 Please check the specified mirror or try a different one.

Template: mirror/noarch
Type: error
# :sl3:
_Description: Architecture not supported
 The specified Parrot archive mirror does not seem to support your
 architecture. Please try a different mirror.


